Network Long Distance sees Q1 charge . Network Long Distance Inc said Thursday it expects a one - time charge of about $ 2 . 3 million in the first quarter ended June 30 , 1997 . The company said the charge will reflect transaction costs related to its mergers with National Teleservices Inc and Eastern Telecom International Corp . Network Long Distance also said that its loss of $ 7 . 8 million in the fiscal year ended March 31 included a non - recurring non - cash provision of $ 6 . 3 million , reflecting the reduced carrying value of previously purchased customer bases and goodwill . 
